<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="The_Dark_Horse_Book_of_the_Dead">The Dark Horse Book of the Dead</span></h3>
<p>This third volume was published June 1, <a href="" title="2005 in comics">2005</a> and featured a new Hellboy story by Mike Mignola as well as a story by <i>Goon</i> creator <a href="" title="Eric Powell (comics)">Eric Powell</a> and a classic tale by <i><a href="" title="Conan the Barbarian">Conan the Barbarian</a></i> creator <a href="" title="Robert E. Howard">Robert E. Howard</a> illustrated by cover artist Gary Gianni.&#60;ref name=&#34;DHDHBD&#34;&#62; &#60;/ref&#62;&#60;ref name=&#34;HBDHBD&#34;&#62;   &#60;/ref&#62;  </p>
<p>In his introduction editor Scott Allie states that this was supposed to be the last book in the series, as he thought he was pushing his luck with three, but greedier minds prevailed and a fourth would follow, which he agreed to because he enjoyed working with the writers and artists involved in the series.&#60;ref name=DHBDBook&#62; &#60;/ref&#62; </p>

